  <prompt>
    Close out the `sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair` project. This task is the final task — it does NOT add new functional work; it captures lessons, marks the project complete, and ensures the repo is hygienic for follow-on projects (per design.md §11.1, Projects 2-5: test architecture, coverage, quality, rigor).

    Five wrap-up actions:
    1. Write `notes/lessons-learned.md` with what went well, what was harder than expected, escalations summary, sibling-coordination outcomes, recommendations for follow-on projects 2-5
    2. Update `README.md` status header from "Planning" (or whatever current state) to "Complete" with closure date
    3. Invoke `/repo-cleanup` skill for repo hygiene audit (per skill: validates structure compliance, removes ephemeral files)
    4. Set `current-task.md` status to "none — project closed"
    5. Final commit: "chore: close sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair project"

    Hard dependency: task 086 (final verification) MUST have passed all 4 verifications and stamped exit-ledger.md as "Final Verification Complete". If 086 has not, this task HALTS.

    NO production code changes. NO test changes. Project hygiene + closure only.
  </prompt>

  <role>AI agent closing out the project with lessons-learned + README update + repo-cleanup + current-task reset.</role>

  <goal>
    Project formally closed. Five outputs:
    - `notes/lessons-learned.md` (new) — written per design §11.1 follow-on-project guidance with sections per design.md §10 effort estimate vs actual, §2.3 sibling coordination outcomes, §4.8 escalation count, and recommendations for Projects 2-5
    - `README.md` (updated) — status header changed from "Planning" or "In Progress" to "Complete" with closure date stamped
    - `/repo-cleanup` skill executed — output documented; any ephemeral files removed
    - `current-task.md` (updated) — status set to "none — project closed"; phase set to "✅ Complete"
    - Final commit message: "chore: close sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair project"
  </goal>

