  <context>
    <background>
      The wrap-up follows the pattern established by `projects/sdap-bff-api-remediation-fix/` close (CLAUDE.md notes "✅ Complete — all in-scope phases delivered; project formally closed 2026-05-26"). The lessons-learned doc is the most important deliverable here — design.md §11.1 explicitly names Projects 2-5 as future work; this project's lessons calibrate the scoping for those (e.g., if rewrite ratio was 4.8% — close to the 5% ceiling — that signals Project 2 architecture split is more urgent than scheduling assumes).

      The `/repo-cleanup` skill validates structure compliance and removes ephemeral files (temp baseline runs that shouldn't survive, scratch markdown files in the project root, etc.). Per the skill, it produces an audit report; this task captures the report's recommendations.

      `current-task.md` reset to "none — project closed" is the canonical signal that no further task work is queued. Future sessions opening this project see the status and either (a) re-open for an additional task per owner direction or (b) move on to a new project.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="086" status="not-started">HARD — final verification MUST have passed (exit ledger stamped "Final Verification Complete")</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <relevant-files>
    <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/notes/lessons-learned.md</file>
